CBRE on behalf of the Parramatta RSL Club (Castle Hill RSL Group), are pleased to present to market 7 Macquarie Street, Parramatta. This terrific mixed-use site presents developers a versatile opportunity in Sydney’s bustling second CBD.

Key attributes of the Site include:
- Large single land holding of 1,874sqm*
- Currently existing as a freestanding carpark
- Zoned B4 – Mixed Use suitable for a range of uses
- Floor Space Ratio of 6:1
- Height Limit of 54 metres
- Parramatta CBD Location moments from transport, amenities and Parramatta Square
- Overlooking the vast greenery of Parramatta Park
- Delayed settlement available

For a copy of the Information Memorandum or to find out more about the opportunity, please contact the exclusive marketing agents listed below.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: PARRAMATTA CBD MIXED USE SITE WITH 3 YEARS DELAYED SETTLEMENT

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE as the exclusive agents are please to offer this fantastic development opportunity in Sydney's booming Parramatta CBD.

The site boasts the following attributes:


• Site area 2,635 sqm (approx.)
• Current FSR 3:1, Proposed FSR 6:1
• Zoning B4 Mixed Use
• 200m from proposed Parramatta light rail
• Located within the Greater Sydney Commission Planning Proposal
• Freehold Commercial Building on a Corner Position

To obtain further information please contact the listing agent.

Location
Parramatta is a major commercial centre of Greater Sydney located approximately 23KM west of the Sydney CBD. .. Recent major upgrades have occurred around the railway station, with the expansion of Westfield Parramatta, the creation of a new transport interchange and the ongoing development of the Parramatta Square local government precinct.

The subject site is located on the southern side of George Street, between Marsden and Church Streets.
Amenities in the vicinity include Westfield shopping centre and Parramatta Railway Station, both of which are approximately 450 metres to the south and the Church Street retail strip, some 50 metres to the west..

Description
The site benefits from a 15 metre* frontage to George Street and is regular in shape. The property is cleared and level and currently used for car parking.

Lot B in DP223477

717* sqm

Parramatta City Council

Property and Development NSW (a division of Property NSW) (PDNSW) has been engaged by  the Minister for Education and Early Childhood Learning (Vendor) to divest part of 34 Hassall Street, Parramatta. CBRE, on behalf of PDNSW and the Vendor, is seeking expressions of interest (EOI) from capable parties interested in delivering Parramatta’s newest precinct.

This is a great opportunity for a developer to capitalise on the significant infrastructure investment currently being made in the Parramatta CBD.

Key Features:
•	Parramatta CBD position
•	Land Area of 5,805qm* approximately (subject to survey)
•	B4 Mixed Use zoning
•	FSR of up to 12:1 (STCA)* 
•	Opposite the future Parramatta Light Rail stop
•	Three street frontages
•	City skyline and district views
                                                 
* The potential FSR is based on the Parramatta CBD Planning Proposal which is subject to approval and gazettal.
                                        
This development opportunity is being offered via a Two Stage Tender process, being:

Stage 1 – Call for Expressions of Interest; and
Stage 2 – Request for Tenders (by invitation only).

All Expressions of Interest must be submitted electronically to www.tenders.nsw.gov.au by 3pm on Friday, 26 March 2021.
